{{Notability|1=Org|date=March 2010}} {{Infobox company | name = LJ Create Ltd. | logo = | type = Privately Held Company | foundation = 1979 | location = 5/6 Francis Way, [[Bowthorpe]], [[Norwich]], [[Norfolk]] | locations = Offices & Facilities in UK & United States | area_served = Worldwide | industry = Education Technology | products = Living with STEM, Exploring STEM, Working with STEM, [[Scantek]], eContent, Tactic, Science Cart, Digiac, EngineeringDiploma.net, Autolab | services = Curriculum Development, Technical Support, Professional Development, Training, Implementation Management | homepage = [http://www.ljcreate.com/ www.ljcreate.com] }}
'''LJ Create Ltd''' is a UK-based company that produces interactive [[educational technology]] for the global market. The company operates in over 60 countries.
==Overview== LJ Create Ltd was established 6 June 1979 when a [[City College Norwich]] lecturer, Larry Rowe, won a local enterprise competition.<ref>BBC Television News: ''LJ Create - 30 years On'', BBC1 September 24th 2009.</ref>
LJ Create makes [[blended learning]] solutions for teaching Science, Engineering and Technology.<ref>{{cite web|url = http://www.excellencegateway.org.uk/page.aspx?o=262032 | title = Jisc Report - Swale Skills Centre, Engineering apprentices use LJ Create to put the spark back into blended learning | work = UK Government Learning and Skills Improvement Service | accessdate = 19 March 2010}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url = http://www.hindu.com/thehindu/edu/2009/08/31/stories/2009083150220200.htm | title = The Hindu 'Make way for an ActivClassroom'. | work = Online edition of India's National Newspaper | accessdate = 19 March 2010 | location=Chennai, India | date=31 August 2009}}</ref> They have become a world leader in STEM resources, manufacturing both hardware and software.{{cn|date=September 2018}}
LJ Create was sold to [[Infinitas Learning]] on 23 January 2012 and became a subsidiary of [[Nelson Thornes]].<ref>{{cite web|url = http://uk.prweb.com/releases/2012/1/prweb9133315.htm | title = Infinitas Learning completes the acquisition of LJ Create Ltd. | work = PR Web | accessdate = 30 January 2012}}</ref> LJ Create was bought on 24 July 2015 by the senior management team, including managing director Chris Rowe who founded the company with his father Larry Rowe in the late 1970s.<ref>{{cite web|url = http://www.edp24.co.uk/business/norwich_s_lj_create_eyes_international_expansion_after_management_buyout_1_4181399 | title = Norwich’s LJ Create eyes international expansion after management buyout | work = PR Web | accessdate = 11 March 2015}}</ref> According to Companies House LJCR1863 LIMITED (previously LJ Create) went in to liquidation in 2017<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://beta.companieshouse.gov.uk/company/00941599|title=LJCR1863 LIMITED - Overview (free company information from Companies House)|website=beta.companieshouse.gov.uk|language=en|access-date=2018-09-07}}</ref> but has since been sold to Creative Learning (Norwich) Ltd., operating out of the same address.
