The '''Norwegian Writers for Children''' ({{lang-no|Norske Barne- og Ungdomsbokforfattere}}, NBU) was founded in 1947. The association, composed of authors who write [[fiction]] for children and young people, promotes the interests of writers of books for children and young people and encourages literature for children and young people. NBU has almost 300 members.
